<div class="intro">
<p>Images will be commonly used within the BYU-I site. The Image element allows users to import images from the assets folder.</p>
</div>
<p style="margin-top: 50px;"><strong style="font-size: 20px;">How to upload Images</strong></p>
<p>In order to upload an image to the assets folder click on the   <a href="http://www.byui.edu/x35738.xml#toolAssets" style="color: #3366ff;" title="Assets" target="_blank"> Assets  button</a> located in the <a href="http://www.byui.edu/x35738.xml#CMS_tool_bar" style="color: #3366ff;" title="CMS tool bar" target="_blank">CMS tool bar</a>. All departments should have a predefined image folder to place images in. If you are not sure where to upload images to, please refer to upper management or technical support.</p>
<span class="title" style="text-decoration: underline;"> </span>
<p style="margin-top: 50px;"><strong style="font-size: 20px;">Interface</strong></p>
<img alt="Image" height="180" src="Images/Internal_Use/Ingeniux_Training/Element Views/Image.png" style="width: 710px;" title="Image" width="800" />
<h4 class="sub_title">Image:</h4>
<p>The Image field is where the user can type the file address of the image file they wish to use.</p>
<p>If needed, the <em>Browse</em> button can be used to display the contents of the assets image folder where a user can select an image. Doing so will insert the file address of the selected image.</p>
<h4 class="sub_title">Width and Height</h4>
<p>The Width and Height fields only display the selected image's width and height. Changing the width and height within these fields does not change the size of the image.</p>
<h4 class="sub_title">Unused Fields</h4>
<ul class="one_line">
<li class="dot">Alt Text:</li>
<li class="dot">Alignment</li>
<li class="dot">Border:</li>
<li class="dot">HSpace:</li>
<li class="dot">VSpace:</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p style="margin-top: 50px;"><strong style="font-size: 20px;">How to Edit a Selected Image (Image Editor)</strong></p>
<p>If a correct file address has been entered in the image field, the image will be displayed within the image field. Double clicking this image will bring up the Image Editor.</p>
<h4 class="sub_title">Image Editor Interface</h4>
<p style="margin-bottom: 3px;">Basic imaging tools are available for user changes, but remember after making changes to accept or reject your changes.</p>
<img alt="Y N" height="20" src="Images/Internal_Use/Ingeniux_Training/Element Views/Image_Yes_No.png" style="margin: 0 5px 3px 10px;" title="Y N" width="50" />
<p style="width: 200px;">These buttons will be provided.</p>
<h4 class="sub_title">Saving</h4>
<ul>
<li>Save Changes - Save changes to current image file</li>
<li>Save As - Save to new image file</li>
<li>Close - Disregard all changes and close editor</li>
</ul>
